- Added depth-2 temp sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0052): root-level `temp_sampler_dispatch.py` is now import-safe outside the SenseWeave package and exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan`. The helpers produce JSON-safe operator output for sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and canonical `/s_new sw_sampler` synth args. `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` builder while preserving existing buffer loading, FX preset, handle-release, fire-and-forget, and sustained lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_temp_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins import safety, meaningful plan/summary output, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2; production sampler dispatch tests and startup identity anchors remain green.

- Added depth-2 PromptClaw memory journal helpers (frac-0051): `promptclaw/memory.py` now exposes a frozen `MemoryEntry` dataclass plus typed helpers `format_run_block`, `parse_memory_log`, and `summarize_memory_log`, and `MemoryStore` gains `entries`, `latest_entry`, and `summary` read-side methods so callers and operator diagnostics can render a single run's memory block, parse the project memory file back into structured entries (run id, title, status, lead, verifier, final phase, body), and emit a JSON-safe aggregate (entry count, latest run id, sorted status counts, sorted lead-agent counts excluding the `n/a` placeholder). `MemoryStore.append_run_summary` now delegates block rendering to `format_run_block` so the on-disk markdown shape stays byte-identical for orchestrator clarification-pause and final-summary writes. `tests/test_promptclaw_memory_depth.py` pins canonical block layout, `n/a` agent fallbacks, append/parse round-trip, empty-input handling, JSON-safe summary aggregation, `n/a` lead exclusion, store read helpers (including missing-file path), and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` remains the regression anchor for end-to-end run behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.


